-- Ladbrokes Makes 70 Pence a Share Bid for Online Casino 888, Telegraph Says
-- B y   G r a n t   S m i t h
-- 2010-12-19T09:34:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-19/ladbrokes-makes-373-million-bid-for-888-sunday-telegraph-says.html
Ladbrokes Plc  bid 240 million pounds
($373 million) for 888 Holdings Plc, the  Sunday Telegraph 
reported, without saying where it got the information.  Ladbrokes bid 70 pence a share for the internet casino and
poker group it tried to acquire four years ago, and may face
rival approaches from Sportingbet Plc, the newspaper said.
Ladbrokes declined to comment, according to the Telegraph.  To contact the reporter on this story:
